                        <quote source="#bib429-1">ܐܰܬܪܐ ܗܘ ܕܰܠܡܰܥܪܒܳܐ ܕܰܦܪܳܬ. ܘܰܠܬܰܝܡܢܳܐ ܡܰܕܢܚܳܝܐ ܕܕܰܝܪ ܐܠܙܘܪ. ܡܶܢ ܐܰܬܪ̈ܘܬܐ ܕܥܪܰܐܩ.</quote>
                    </desc><desc xml:lang="ar">
                        <quote source="#bib429-2">بلد غربي الفرات جنوبي شرقي دير الزور من بلاد العراق.</quote>
                    </desc><desc xml:lang="en">
                        <quote source="#bib429-3">a town in Iraq, west of the Euphrates and southeast of Dayr al-Zur.</quote>
                    </desc><desc xml:lang="en" xml:id="abstract-en-429429-NaN">“[I]n the Middle Ages also ʿānāt , and in Turkish official usage ʿana —is a town of modern ʿIrāḳ situated on the Euphrates right bank (41° 58’ E, 34° 28’ N.), some 245 kilometers southeast of Dayr al-Zūr and 148 north-west of Hīt.” (S.H. Longrigg)</desc><desc xml:lang="ar" xml:id="abstract-en-429429-NaN">
